 Asia for a season. (Act 19:22)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I2996'),('02997',2,'02997','M','0 @02997@ INDI\n1 NAME Demetrius //\n2 GIVN Demetrius\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE For a certain man named Demetrius, a silversmith, which made silver shrines for Diana, brought no small gain unto the craftsmen; (Act 19:24)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I2997'),('02998',2,'02998','M','0 @02998@ INDI\n1 NAME Diana //\n2 GIVN Diana\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE For a certain man named Demetrius, a silversmith, which made silver shrines for Diana, brought no small gain unto the craftsmen; (Act 19:24)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I2998'),('02999',2,'02999','M','0 @02999@ INDI\n1 NAME Gaius //\n2 GIVN Gaius\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And the whole city was filled with confusion: and having caught Gaius and Aristarchus, men of Macedonia, Paul\'s companions in travel, they rushed with one accord into the theatre. (Act 19:29)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I2999'),('03000',2,'03000','M','0 @03000@ INDI\n1 NAME Aristarchus //\n2 GIVN Aristarchus\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And the whole city was filled with confusion: and having caught Gaius and Aristarchus, men of Macedonia, Paul\'s companions in travel, they rushed with one accord into the theatre. (Act 19:29)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3000'),('03001',2,'03001','M','0 @03001@ INDI\n1 NAME Alexander //\n2 GIVN Alexander\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And they drew Alexander out of the multitude, the Jews putting him forward. And Alexander beckoned with the hand, and would have made his defence unto the people. (Act 19:33)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3001'),('03002',2,'03002','M','0 @03002@ INDI\n1 NAME Sopater - Sosipater //\n2 GIVN Sopater - Sosipater\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And there accompanied him into Asia Sopater of Berea; and of the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timotheus; and of Asia, Tychicus and Trophimus. (Act 20:4)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3002'),('03003',2,'03003','M','0 @03003@ INDI\n1 NAME Secundus //\n2 GIVN Secundus\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And there accompanied him into Asia Sopater of Berea; and of the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timotheus; and of Asia, Tychicus and Trophimus. (Act 20:4)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3003'),('03004',2,'03004','M','0 @03004@ INDI\n1 NAME Gaius //\n2 GIVN Gaius\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And there accompanied him into Asia Sopater of Berea; and of the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timotheus; and of Asia, Tychicus and Trophimus. (Act 20:4)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3004'),('03005',2,'03005','M','0 @03005@ INDI\n1 NAME Tychicus //\n2 GIVN Tychicus\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And there accompanied him into Asia Sopater of Berea; and of the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timotheus; and of Asia, Tychicus and Trophimus. (Act 20:4)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3005'),('03006',2,'03006','M','0 @03006@ INDI\n1 NAME Trophimus //\n2 GIVN Trophimus\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And there accompanied him into Asia Sopater of Berea; and of the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timotheus; and of Asia, Tychicus and Trophimus. (Act 20:4)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3006'),('03007',2,'03007','M','0 @03007@ INDI\n1 NAME Eutychus //\n2 GIVN Eutychus\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And there sat in a window a certain young man named Eutychus, being fallen into a deep sleep: and as Paul was long preaching, he sunk down with sleep, and fell down from the third loft, and was taken up dead. (Act 20:9)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3007'),('03008',2,'03008','M','0 @03008@ INDI\n1 NAME Mnason //\n2 GIVN Mnason\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE There went with us also certain of the disciples of Caesarea, and brought with them one Mnason of Cyprus, an old disciple, with whom we should lodge. (Act 21:16)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3008'),('03009',2,'03009','M','0 @03009@ INDI\n1 NAME Ananias //\n2 GIVN Ananias\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And the high priest Ananias commanded them that stood by him to smite him on the mouth. (Act 23:2)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3009'),('03010',2,'03010','M','0 @03010@ INDI\n1 NAME Felix //\n2 GIVN Felix\n1 SEX M\n1 FAMS @0301003013@\n1 NOTE And provide them beasts, that they may set Paul on, and bring him safe unto Felix the governor. (Act 23:24)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3010'),('03011',2,'03011','M','0 @03011@ INDI\n1 NAME Claudius Lysias //\n2 GIVN Claudius Lysias\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE Claudius Lysias unto the most excellent governor Felix sendeth greeting. (Act 23:26)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3011'),('03012',2,'03012','M','0 @03012@ INDI\n1 NAME Tertullus //\n2 GIVN Tertullus\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And after five days Ananias the high priest descended with the elders, and with a certain orator named Tertullus, who informed the governor against Paul. (Act 24:1)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3012'),('03013',2,'03013','F','0 @03013@ INDI\n1 NAME Drusilla //\n2 GIVN Drusilla\n1 SEX F\n1 FAMS @0301003013@\n1 NOTE And after certain days, when Felix came with his wife Drusilla, which was a Jewess, he sent for Paul, and heard him concerning the faith in Christ. (Act 24:24)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3013'),('03014',2,'03014','M','0 @03014@ INDI\n1 NAME Porcius Festus //\n2 GIVN Porcius Festus\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE But after two years Porcius Festus came into Felix\' room: and Felix, willing to shew the Jews a pleasure, left Paul bound. (Act 24:27)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3014'),('03015',2,'03015','M','0 @03015@ INDI\n1 NAME Agrippa //\n2 GIVN Agrippa\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And after certain days king Agrippa and Bernice came unto Caesarea to salute Festus. (Act 25:13)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3015'),('03016',2,'03016','M','0 @03016@ INDI\n1 NAME Bernice //\n2 GIVN Bernice\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And after certain days king Agrippa and Bernice came unto Caesarea to salute Festus. (Act 25:13)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3016'),('03017',2,'03017','M','0 @03017@ INDI\n1 NAME Julius //\n2 GIVN Julius\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE And when it was determined that we should sail into Italy, they delivered Paul and certain other prisoners unto one named Julius, a centurion of Augustus\' band. (Act 27:1)\n1 RIN BIBLE_I3017'),('03018',2,'03018','M','0 @03018@ INDI\n1 NAME Publius //\n2 GIVN Publius\n1 SEX M\n1 NOTE In the same quarters were possessions of the chief man of the island, whose name was Publius; who received